Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.91,0:00:37.99,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,（芝加哥）
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.83,0:00:44.62,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,妈妈生病了 就这么突然发生了\N{\r原文字幕}Mummy got sick. It happened just like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.67,0:00:49.00,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,没人可以帮上忙\N{\r原文字幕}Nobody could stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.17,0:00:52.96,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,这不公平 没有什么原因\N{\r原文字幕}It isn't fair. There's no reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.13,0:00:58.85,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,再不停问原因 只会令人发疯\N{\r原文字幕}And if we start asking why, we'll go crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.21,0:01:26.12,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,只要放进任何一个微波炉 五分钟就可以了\N{\r原文字幕}Five minutes in the microwave. Any one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.05,0:01:31.41,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,你知道怎样弄果汁吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Do you know how to make juice?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.93,0:01:37.92,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,放进微波炉五分钟\N{\r原文字幕}Microwave. Five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.74,0:01:58.23,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,给 这是我的心理医生 给他打个电话吧\N{\r原文字幕}Here. It's my shrink. Call him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.29,0:02:11.46,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,这是丧偶互助会\N{\r原文字幕}Loss of Spouse Support Group.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.63,0:02:17.09,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,芝加哥癌症病人家属支援会 父母失去另一半的\N{\r原文字幕}Chicago Cancer Family Network. Parents without Partners.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.26,0:02:21.63,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,拥抱自己 拥抱朋友 拥抱一位心理医生\N{\r原文字幕}"Hug Yourself", "Hug a Friend", "Hug a Shrink"...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.81,0:02:27.73,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,努力工作 工作能拯救你\N唯有工作能帮你度过这状况\N{\r原文字幕}Work hard, that'll save you. Only work will see you through this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.78,0:02:37.99,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,别介意 一位刚刚丧偶的男人就会这样\N{\r原文字幕}Don't mind him, he's just a guy who's lost his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.08,0:02:46.32,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,我想我真正需要的是改变\N{\r原文字幕}What I think we really need is... change.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.50,0:02:51.92,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,好主意 放几周假 跟乔纳去钓个鱼\N{\r原文字幕}Good idea. Take a few weeks off, take Jonah fishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.72,0:02:58.13,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,不 是真的改变 新城市\N{\r原文字幕}No, real change. A new city.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.18,0:03:04.22,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,一个新地方 让我不再想起玛姬的地方\N{\r原文字幕}Some place where I don't think of Maggie at every corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.19,0:03:07.27,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,（瑞格里球场\N芝加哥《小熊队》球场）
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.86,0:03:12.98,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,你要去哪？\N{\r原文字幕}Where are you gonna go?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.24,0:03:20.58,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,我在考虑去西雅图\N{\r原文字幕}I was thinking about Seattle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.41,0:03:26.41,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,过几个月 你会再和女人约会 你会遇到心仪的对象的\N{\r原文字幕}In a few months, you'll be seeing women. You'll meet someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.59,0:03:33.38,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,对 向前看 这正是我想做的 几个月后 我会复原 重新长个心\N{\r原文字幕}Move on, fine, that's what I'll do. I'll just grow a new heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.88,0:03:39.80,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-山姆 对不起 我不是这意思\N-我知道 只是有些事情一生一次足矣\N{\r原文字幕}- Sam, I'm sorry, I didn't mean... - I know. But it can't happen twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.42,0:03:41.67,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,♫ Jimmy Dante: "As Time Goes By"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.84,0:03:45.64,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,♪ You must remember this, ♪ ♪ A kiss is still a kiss ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.35,0:03:48.76,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,♪ A sigh is just a sigh ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.39,0:03:56.52,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,♪ The fundamental things apply ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.44,0:03:59.44,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,♪ As time goes by ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.03,0:04:06.53,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,♪ And when two lovers woo ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.28,0:04:09.45,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,♪ They still say "I love you" ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.08,0:04:12.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,♪ On that you can rely ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.21,0:04:20.13,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,♪ No matter what the future brings ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.34,0:04:23.42,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,♪ As time goes by ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.14,0:04:30.72,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,♪ Moonlight and love songs ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.27,0:04:33.14,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,♪ Never out of date ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.19,0:04:36.23,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,♪ Hearts full of passion ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.81,0:04:38.94,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,♪ Jealousy and hate ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.90,0:04:44.61,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,♪ Woman needs man ♪ ♪ And man must have his mate ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.24,0:04:49.28,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,♪ That no one can deny ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.20,0:04:53.58,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,♪ It's still the same old story ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.87,0:04:56.54,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,♪ A fight for love and glory ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.08,0:04:59.54,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,♪ A case of do or die ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.09,0:05:07.68,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,♪ The world ♪ ♪ Will always welcome lovers ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.18,0:05:15.10,原文字幕,,0,0,0,,♪ As time goes by ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.54,0:05:23.30,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,（巴尔的摩\N18个月后）
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.42,0:05:34.54,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-红发的高女人是你的表姐艾琳 -一脸失望那个就是她\N{\r原文字幕}- The tall redhead is cousin Irene. - You'll see her disappointed look.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.72,0:05:41.51,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-哈洛则是跟女秘书有染\N-直到艾琳的狗病死\N{\r原文字幕}- Harold ran off with the secretary. - Until Irene had the dog put down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.68,0:05:46.52,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,你的哥哥丹尼斯是教授 在约翰斯·霍普金斯\N{\r原文字幕}Your brother Dennis is professor at Johns Hopkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.69,0:05:52.31,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-她老婆是…贝琪\N-世上最难缠的人\N{\r原文字幕}- He's married to... Betsy. - The most competitive woman ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.49,0:05:56.98,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-我怎能记住那么多事情呢？\N-华特 你可以的\N{\r原文字幕}- How will I remember all this? - Walter, you will!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.09,0:06:13.58,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-你的米顿叔叔赔掉所有钱\N-还有其他人的钱\N{\r原文字幕}- Uncle Milton lost all his money... - And some other people's.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.76,0:06:18.34,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,因为骗局 更别提国税局或监狱\N{\r原文字幕}...in a pyramid scheme. Don't mention the IRS or the prisons.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.51,0:06:21.88,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,你妈叫芭芭拉\N你爸是克里夫\N{\r原文字幕}Your mother's Barbara, your father's Cliff...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.06,0:06:25.93,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-我爸收集电动火车\N-真的？\N{\r原文字幕}- He has electric trains. - Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.11,0:06:29.02,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,我算乘龙快婿吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Am I what they had in mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.19,0:06:33.44,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,华特 他们会喜欢你的\N{\r原文字幕}Walter, they're gonna love you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.95,0:06:41.03,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,大家注意 安妮有事要宣布\N{\r原文字幕}Everybody, Annie has an announcement.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.21,0:06:44.95,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,华特和我订婚了\N{\r原文字幕}Walter and I are engaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.59,0:06:53.17,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,谢谢 谢谢\N{\r原文字幕}Thank you. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.56,0:07:01.09,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,恭喜了 华特\N{\r原文字幕}Congratulations, Walter.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.85,0:07:04.97,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,上帝保佑你\N{\r原文字幕}Bless you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.61,0:07:11.65,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-你还好吧？\N-大概是花\N{\r原文字幕}- Are you all right? - Maybe it's the flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.82,0:07:16.15,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-那把花移开\N-不 我要打喷嚏了\N{\r原文字幕}- We'll move them. - No! I feel terrible, sneezing now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.33,0:07:21.41,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-偏偏这时候打喷嚏\N-他对什么都过敏\N{\r原文字幕}- This is a very important moment. - He's allergic to everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.58,0:07:25.07,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,我对蜜蜂过敏\N{\r原文字幕}Bees. I'm allergic to bees.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.25,0:07:31.00,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,不管哪种蜜蜂 我们随身携带肾上腺素\N{\r原文字幕}He's allergic to all bees. We have to take adrenalin with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.17,0:07:37.64,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-吃一颗小果仁\N-我的脑袋就会肿胀 然后会昏过去\N{\r原文字幕}- If he eats just a bit of a nut... - My head swells, and I drop dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.81,0:07:42.01,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-哈洛碰到蜜蜂也一样\N-我和你妈结婚时吃鲑鱼\N{\r原文字幕}- It's the same with him and bees. - We had salmon at our wedding.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.19,0:07:47.98,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-那可是婚礼的必备佳肴\N-我对鲑鱼不会过敏\N{\r原文字幕}- A wedding without salmon is... - I'm not allergic to salmon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.15,0:07:50.64,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,但是也难讲\N{\r原文字幕}But you never know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.82,0:07:54.94,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-没错\N-哈洛不是每次都对蜜蜂过敏\N{\r原文字幕}- You never know. - He wasn't always allergic to bees.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.12,0:08:02.41,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们开香槟是为了庆祝什么？\N-庆祝米顿叔叔假释\N{\r原文字幕}- What did we do with our champagne? - Uncle Milton's parole.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.58,0:08:07.83,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-安妮 你什么时候结婚？\N-六月初 在花园举行\N{\r原文字幕}- When are you getting married? - Early June, in the garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.00,0:08:15.00,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-哈洛和蜜蜂怎么办？\N-我对蜜蜂过敏\N{\r原文字幕}- What about Harold and bees? - I'm allergic to bees.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.18,0:08:18.89,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,冷鲜鱼、黄瓜沙拉、草莓\N{\r原文字幕}Cold salmon, cucumber salad, strawberries.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.06,0:08:24.22,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,我对草莓过敏\N{\r原文字幕}I'm afraid I am allergic to strawberries.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.40,0:08:28.51,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,你没关系吗？\N{\r原文字幕}Is this all right with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.69,0:08:34.53,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,今天我是全世界最幸运的人\N{\r原文字幕}I'm the luckiest man-man-man on the face of the earth-earth-earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.70,0:08:40.74,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-陆·葛瑞(加里·库珀饰)的台词是…\N-《洋基的骄傲》(1942)…\N{\r原文字幕}- That's Lou Gehrig's line from... - Pride of the Yankees.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.91,0:08:45.66,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-《洋基的骄傲》里头的\N-棒球电影 这句话很经典\N{\r原文字幕}- Pride of the Yankees! - Baseball. An historical reference.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.83,0:08:50.58,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,我提议举杯贺喜 敬我妹妹\N{\r原文字幕}I would like to propose a toast. To my kid sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.76,0:08:54.72,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,敬华特和我的宝贝\N{\r原文字幕}To Walter and my baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.10,0:09:01.93,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,大家快吃 菜都凉了\N{\r原文字幕}Please eat, before it gets cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.52,0:09:10.48,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,找到了 历史学会想要 我都不肯给\N{\r原文字幕}Here it is. I wouldn't give it to the Historical Society.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.65,0:09:15.40,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-哦 妈！\N-我知道这款式又在流行了\N{\r原文字幕}- Oh, Mum... - These things are back in fashion.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.57,0:09:18.74,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,外婆的结婚礼服\N{\r原文字幕}Grandmother's dress.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.91,0:09:25.87,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-他人不错\N-我知道 他很棒吧？\N{\r原文字幕}- He's a lovely man, Annie. - He is, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.13,0:09:32.71,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,而且是优秀运动员 我们要去华盛顿特区见他的父母\N{\r原文字幕}And he's a wonderful athlete. We're going to DC to see his parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.88,0:09:37.00,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-你们怎么认识的？\N-说来可笑\N{\r原文字幕}- How did it happen? - It's silly, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.18,0:09:42.35,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,我们在公司见过 他是出版商代表\N{\r原文字幕}I'd seen him at the office. He's the associate publisher.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.52,0:09:46.18,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,有一天我们刚巧 向同一家店订三明治\N{\r原文字幕}We had both ordered sandwiches...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.36,0:09:50.52,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,他拿到我的 让他过敏的生菜番茄全麦包\N{\r原文字幕}...and he got my tomato on wheat, which he's allergic to.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.69,0:09:55.15,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,而我却拿了他的 太神奇了 对吗？\N{\r原文字幕}And I got his tomato on white. Amazing, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.32,0:10:00.32,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,每天做多少决定 随便一个便能改变你的一生\N{\r原文字幕}You make a million decisions, and a sandwich changes your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.50,0:10:03.24,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,命中注定\N{\r原文字幕}Destiny takes a hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.42,0:10:09.13,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,我们不能接受不如意的事情发生 所以才发明命运\N{\r原文字幕}We invented destiny, because we don't want things to be accidental.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.30,0:10:14.42,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,但你怎解释你们叫了 几乎同样的东西 除了面包外？\N{\r原文字幕}Then why did you order the same sandwich except for the bread?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.59,0:10:21.56,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,有多少人只吃生菜番茄三明治 连点肉都不加？\N{\r原文字幕}How many people like tomato without something else, like tuna?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.77,0:10:25.64,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,这不是预兆 纯属巧合\N{\r原文字幕}It wasn't a sign. It was a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.81,0:10:30.10,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,我和家人到大西洋城 你爸在那当侍者\N{\r原文字幕}I was in Atlantic City, where Cliff was a waiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.28,0:10:34.74,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,他当晚恰好与人调班\N{\r原文字幕}He wasn't supposed to work that night. What if he hadn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.91,0:10:42.75,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,他请我到码头来午夜漫步\N我说过上千次了 不过我才不管\N{\r原文字幕}He asked me to take a midnight walk. I told you this a million times.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.92,0:10:51.13,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,他握着我的手\N我看着 分不出谁是谁的手指\N{\r原文字幕}He held my hand. I looked down and couldn't tell our fingers apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.30,0:10:55.88,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-我心里便明白了\N-什么？\N{\r原文字幕}- And I knew. - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.60,0:11:03.22,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-什么？\N-魔力 是魔力\N{\r原文字幕}- What? - It was magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.81,0:11:05.14,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,这就是魔力\N{\r原文字幕}Magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.31,0:11:12.44,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,我知道我们将终生幸福厮守\N就像你对华特一样\N{\r原文字幕}I knew we'd be together forever. Just like you and Walter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.61,0:11:16.98,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,华特 挺正式的名字\N{\r原文字幕}Walter. It's quite a formal name.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.74,0:11:23.91,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,我还知道我和你爸…\N{\r原文字幕}I knew that your father and I would have a wonderful time in...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.08,0:11:27.58,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,在床上会很合的来\N你们是这么叫的吧\N{\r原文字幕}...the sack, I believe you call it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.75,0:11:34.04,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,是过了几年才水乳交融\N{\r原文字幕}It took years before it worked like clockwork. It takes time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.22,0:11:39.34,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们已经…\N-没关系 感觉如何？\N{\r原文字幕}- We already... - Fine, fine. How's it working?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.52,0:11:44.56,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-水乳交融\N-喔 亲爱的\N{\r原文字幕}- Like clockwork. - Oh, honey...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.86,0:11:51.65,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-这是预兆\N-你又不信\N{\r原文字幕}- It's a sign. - You don't believe in signs.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.45,0:12:00.74,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,他们很喜欢你 如我所料\N{\r原文字幕}They loved you. I told you they would.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.91,0:12:04.28,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-我爱你\N-我爱你 华特\N{\r原文字幕}- I love you. - I love you, Walter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.13,0:12:11.37,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-你有小名吗？\N-没有\N{\r原文字幕}Did anyone ever call you anything other than Walter?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.55,0:12:17.92,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-小时候也没有？\N-没有\N{\r原文字幕}- Not even when you were young? - Not even when I was young.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.10,0:12:22.81,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-确定不搭我的车回去吗？\N-我周五怎么回巴尔的摩？\N{\r原文字幕}- Don't you want to drive with me? - Then I can't get back on Friday.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.98,0:12:28.89,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,我忘记拿送你继母的礼忘了 等我们老了\N{\r原文字幕}I forgot your stepmother's present. When we're old and gray...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.07,0:12:35.28,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,你得提醒我戴假牙 这样我出门就不会忘了\N{\r原文字幕}...you must remind me to put my teeth in, so I don't go out without them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.45,0:12:38.36,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,-我等你\N-等我 好\N{\r原文字幕}- I'll wait. - You'll wait? Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.54,0:12:43.83,译文字幕,,0,0,0,,别等了 你先走吧 我就比你晚10分钟\N{\r原文字幕}No, go ahead. We're late anyway. I'll be ten minutes behind you.
